  • Constructor Details

    • BreakerSwerveDriveConfig

      public BreakerSwerveDriveConfig​(double maxForwardVel, double maxSidewaysVel, double maxAngVel, double moduleAnglekP, double moduleAnglekI, double moduleAngleKd, double moduleVelkP, double moduleVelkI, double moduleVelKd, double moduleVelKf, double driveMotorGearRatioToOne, double wheelDiameter, double moduleWheelSpeedDeadband, double maxAttainableModuleWheelSpeed, BreakerArbitraryFeedforwardProvider arbitraryFeedforwardProvider, edu.wpi.first.math.geometry.Translation2d... wheelPositionsRelativeToCenter)
      The overall configuration for a Breaker swerve drivetrain holding all constants, must be passed in.
      Parameters:
      maxForwardVel - Max forward strafe velocity of drivetrain in m/s.
      maxSidewaysVel - Max horizontal strafe velocity of drivetrain in m/s.
      maxAngVel - Max angular velocity of the drivetrain in rad/s.
      moduleAnglekP - Swerve module angular kP (for PID).
      moduleAnglekI - Swerve module angular kI (for PID).
      moduleAngleKd - Swerve module angular kD (for PID).
      moduleVelkP - Swerve module drive kP (for PIDF).
      moduleVelkI - Swerve module drive kI (for PIDF).
      moduleVelKd - Swerve module drive kD (for PIDF).
      moduleVelKf - Swerve module drive kF (for PIDF).
      arbitraryFeedforwardProvider -
      driveMotorGearRatioToOne - Gear ratio of swerve modules.
      wheelDiameter - The diameter of your module's wheels in inches.
      wheelspeedDeadband - The min value (+/-) in m/s^2 that each modules wheel speed can be set too before being ingored
      maxAttainableModuleWheelSpeed - The physical maximum speed (in m/s^2) your swerve modules are capable of achiving
      wheelPositionsRelativeToCenter - Position of each module relative to the robot's center as Translation2d ojects, must be in the same order as their respective modules are added to your BreakerSwerveDrive object.
